    "en": {
      "title": "Marcos visits earthquake victims",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ferdinand Marcos has come with other government officials to observe the areas affected by the severe earthquake that affected the province of Abra in the Philippines.",
        "Marcos said during a briefing on the situation in the provincial capital, Bangud, that the government would provide aid to the affected people.",
        "A strong earthquake of magnitude 7 struck Abra Province and four people have died and at least 131 people have been injured.",
        "After the earthquake, the country's government has acted to immediately send rescue and relief teams to Abra."
      ],
